transcript.text: Hi, we are happy to showcase our new product option enhancements.
Admin only product option option won't be visible in price calculator but we'll calculate price, calculate weight with number of pages.
This feature especially work for booklet kind of products.
Set product specific setup, cost validation and text box type product option.
Create formula and use them directly as variable.
Let's discuss all the features 1 by 1.
Let's discuss admin only product option.
Go to the product option under products.
We have created admin only product options.
What does admin only product option means?
Like you can create product option with admin only feature where option won't be visible at front end in price calculator but the price will be calculated as per the created formula.
For example, you can see we have created this product option named as package creasing cost and type selected as admin only.
Also while you are selecting admin only then it will only work with formula.
Base multipliers will not work in this scenario.
Let's see how it reflects at front end.
You can see the product with size, quantity and printing side.
But when you see assigned option inside the admin, there are three product options assigned to this product named as package, printing cost and Package creasing cost.
As these are admin only options so they are not reflecting at the front end but the price is being calculated.
Now the second one is calculate weight with number of pages.
To understand this concept let us show you one product named as booklet.
So here you can see there are two paper types 310 GSM and 410 GSM.
Customer can put any number of pages.
So how we can calculate weight with number of pages along with its paper type.
Let's understand how we can set this in admin.
Inside admin we have created 2 product option named as number of pages and paper type.
When you go to paper type product option here you can select multiply weight with custom text box where you need to select number of pages.
After that you need to put weight of 1 page for both attributes.

Now to calculate weight we are using 1 formula which you can see on screen option Weight multiply by text box value multiply by quantity plus text box weight multiply by text box value multiply by quantity option weight will be this value which we have entered here 310 GSM and 410 GSM text box value will be entered by customer which is number of pages in quantity is number of books and text box weight will the weight which has been entered over here in number of pages product option.
By using this formula weight will be calculated.
The next feature is set product specific setup cost in product option while you are adding in product option.
For example let's say when you are adding paper type you can add setup cost for attributes let's say $15.00 for 310 GSM and $15.00 for 410 GSM.
While assigning this option to any of the product you can change setup cost in product specific.
Then next feature is validation and text box type product option while you are creating any of the product option with text box.
For example you can see as we have created product option named as number of pages.
So here you can see we can set minimum value along with it we can set default value with intervals.
So here 4 is the default value and two is the interval.
Also you can set up to value.
Let's see how you can create formula and use them directly as variable.
Under product option you can see formula in top right corner click on formula.
Here you can create as many formulas as you want.

For example we have created 1 formula for single fold, increase length and formulas width, multiply by height, multiply by depth, multiply by 4 and variable name as SFCL which we can use directly as variable while creating product option.
Let's see how we can assign this variable go to package creasing cost and edit it.
And here while creating formula we can directly use SFCL as variable.
So in that way you can create your own formula and use them as variable.
Hope you like all product option enhancements.
These feature will help you to configure products at next level.
If you have any more queries, please contact us at support onprintshop.com.
